===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[mæl|mǣl]]'', from Germanic ''*mēlo-'', from Indo-European ''*mē-'' ‘to measure’.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[maal]]'', German ''[[Mal]]'' ‘time’, ''[[Mahl]]'' ‘meal’; and (''from Indo-European'') with Greek [[μέτρον]], Latin ''[[mensus]]'', Russian [[мера]], Lithuanian ''[[metas|mẽtas]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# [[food]] that is prepared and [[eat]]en, usually at a specific time (e.g. breakfast = morning meal, lunch = noon meal, etc)

